Package <Unnamed>

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Chainable
    The Chainable interface provides public methods for connecting Chainable objects one another, and passing data between them.
    Filter
    Interface for filter objects.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdderFilter
    The AdderFilter adds points from its two inputs and produces a DataStream object containing the sums.
    DataStream
    The DataStream objects is an abstraction of an ArrayList of Double objects.
    Plotter
    The Plotter class is responsible for starting the flow of data from the bottom of the filter chain that will eventually be received by the Plotter object via its two inputs.
    ScalerFilter
    The ScalerFilter holds one Chainable input and performs the following operation on that input data: gain * x_i + base
    StreamSet
    StreamSet object has methods for transforming .csv files into an ArrayList of DataStream objects, where a DataStream objects holds all of the values in one column of the file.
    TestMain
    This class showcases the most basic functionality of the plotter using no filters; two data streams mapped directly to the plotter's inputs.
    TestMain2
    This class showcases the functionality of the AdderFilter class.
    TestMain3
    This class showcases the functionality of the ScalerFilter class.
    TestMain4
    This method showcases the combination of multiple filter objects into a chain.
